data.title: Paris – December 3
data.text:
Mickael De Sa

Regional Head of Ecommerce - Allianz Trade en France

In charge of the development of digital partnerships and new distribution channels for insurance solutions via API within Euler Hermes, a subsidiary of the Allianz group. Ability to establish contacts with Startup environments (Fintech and Marketplace) as well as internally in order to coordinate and deliver digital solutions transforming the market approach and existing products.Previously, expert in the management of commercial and marketing activity through various consulting missions in CRM and BI on the optimization of performance in various sectors such as industry, luxury, pharmaceuticals and finance. These past experiences allow me to quickly identify potential markets and ROI for digital products.Participation in the Digital Partner program with a member of the Euler Hermes Board of Management to prepare the digital transformation and the skills development of the group's employees. Presentation of the results during a pitch at the IMM – International Management Meeting in front of the Euler Hermes Management Top 100.

Claire Lebarz

Chief Data & AI Officer - Malt

Building AI and data products for the last 10 years.

When I was in academia, economic empowerment was core to my research. I was looking at the impact of rising inequality of income and wealth, and wanted to shift from analyzing households' balancesheets to improving them. I spent the following 10+ years in San Francisco working on developing marketplaces that enable people to make better use of their assets : their cars (at Turo), their homes (at Airbnb). At Airbnb, we also focused a lot on enabling people to live from their passion with experiences. I have now moved back to France to be closer to my family and contribute to another disrupting marketplace, Malt, enabling people to make the best decisions about their most important asset: their human capital, their talent and their time.

Disruption and innovation often come with a dark side too, even with the best company mission. This is why I love data roles, because we can see first hand what's going on and nudge the organization. Ethical data use and AI is also a significant challenge, on which we need more brains. Join me in this adventure!

Rafik Ferroukh

Software Solutions Architect & SAFe® Agilist - Allianz

I am a Solution/Software Architect with over eight years of experience in designing and developing custom digital products to meet the specific needs of clients and the company. Holding a master's degree in Software Engineering and a SAFe® Agilist certification, I have a strong command of key concepts such as API, Microservices, EDA, and DevSecOps, as well as the most commonly used frameworks and tools in the field, including Java, SpringBoot, and Angular.

At Allianz, I have contributed to the coordination of cloud, enterprise, and business architectures, the monitoring of international-scale subjects, and the facilitation of IT and business communities. I am also an ambassador and maintainer of the Craft Community (France and Global), as well as a speaker at events such as API Days, ParisJUG, Student schools, universities and Allianz internal craft sessions. Passionate about creating innovative solutions, I am committed to knowledge sharing and inclusion, as evidenced by the founding of "IT Pour Tous", an event I launched in 2019.

Michal Valko

Research Scientist at Inria - Principal Engineer, LLama Team, GenAI at Meta

Michal is a machine learning scientist in DeepMind Paris, tenured researcher at Inria, and the lecturer of the master course Graphs in Machine Learning at l'ENS Paris-Saclay. Michal is primarily interested in designing algorithms that would require as little human supervision as possible. This means 1) reducing the “intelligence” that humans need to input into the system and 2) minimizing the data that humans need to spend inspecting, classifying, or “tuning” the algorithms. That is why he is working on methods and settings that are able to deal with minimal feedback, such as deep reinforcement learning, bandit algorithms, or self-supervised learning. Michal is actively working on representation learning and building worlds models. He is also working on deep (reinforcement) learning algorithm that have some theoretical underpinning. He has also worked on sequential algorithms with structured decisions where exploiting the structure leads to provably faster learning. He received his Ph.D. in 2011 from the University of Pittsburgh under the supervision of Miloš Hauskrecht and after was a postdoc of Rémi Munos before taking a permanent position at Inria in 2012.

Jean Baptiste Kempf

Creator of VLC - CEO of VideoLAN

Technology and Free Software enthusiast with a wide scientific background.

CTO, Tech Advisor, Startups Board Member, President of startups and Open Source NGO.

During my life, I've been working on numerous aspects of Computer Science: from Open Source development in major and minor projects to System and Network administration, Hardware design, High Performance Computing, IT support and Information Systems architecture, but also leading large engineering teams and actually delivering projects to numerous users.

Leading the VLC media player and VideoLAN projects brought me a different set of skills, managing most of the non-technical sides of those projects. Project and community management, press relations, IP and other open source skillsets.

Lately, I've created a few startups and have been leading large technical teams as CTO or VP-Eng.

Djalel Benbouzid

AI Governance, Phd - Volkswagen

As the leader tasked with defining AI governance policies and methods, my primary focus is to ensure compliance with the AI Act and foster ethical, legal, and trustworthy AI practices across the organization.

With over 10 years of experience in the field of machine learning, I have developed a deep expertise in generative models, trustworthy AI, and AI governance, as well as a strong passion for teaching, sharing insights, and engaging in effective communication.

Lately, I helped found and later managed the etami consortium, a European project that aims to advance the state of the art in ethical and trustworthy artificial machine intelligence. I oversaw the coordination, collaboration, and dissemination of the project's activities and outcomes, involving partners from academia, industry, and civil society.

I have always been deeply involved in various open science and open research projects, always seeking novel collaborations and fields to explore.

Julien Salvi

Lead Android Engineer - Aircall

Lead Android Engineer at Aircall where we are building the best phone system for modern business. Former CINEMUR and Innovorder.

About me:

• Android & Kotlin lover.

• Having a great interest in UI/UX to bring the best experience to an application (user focus).

• Team builder

• Meetup active member and Organizer at Paris Android User Group / Android Makers.

• International speaker to share my experiences on Android and Kotlin.

• Interests in backend dev with Kotlin (past experiences with PHP/Scala).

Tech talks:

• All talks and associated material can be found on Github: https://github.com/Oleur/SpeakerTimeline

Tech posts:

• All articles are available on Medium: https://juliensalvi.medium.com/

"LEARN, SHARE, REPEAT"

Hamida Rebai

Cloud Solutions Architect - Revenu Quebec

I am Rebaï Hamida, a software architect, and developer who like to build open-source projects, write articles, and learn and teach best practices. you can find out in my blog: https://didourebai.medium.com/Innovative Software engineer: hands-on, competent software engineer, passionate and proficient C# developer, offering more than 12 years of experience in the full software development lifecycle – from concept through delivery of next-generation applications and customized solutions, producing code to a consistently high standard and testing software across a variety of platforms.Expert in advanced development methodologies, tools, and processes contributing to the design and roll-out of cutting-edge software applications.Known for excellent troubleshooting skills – able to analyze code and engineer well-researched, cost-effective and responsive solutions.

Jean Burellier

Principal Engineer, Platform Team Lead - Sanofi

Being associated with the industry since 2012, I have worked as a Developer, Leader, Architect and now Principal Engineer to build, architect and improve solutions based on APIs and real time communication.

I have been thanked for my work around automation of processes allowing the companies to greatly increase the efficiency of their workflows while improving the developer experience and the quality in the final product. My colleagues know me as a good communicator who likes to use an interactive approach for understanding the requirements and solving problems of varied scope.Working with a plethora of roles - both technical and business - such as lead architect, staff engineer, project manager and CxO but also legal team I have been able to develop keen eyes for various technicalities which helped me in maximizing our products impact's for our customers.

Pierre-Olivier Patin

VP / CTO Cloud & DevOps - Sogeti

As a Cloud Technology Officer, I am seeking to understand the context of a business, the organization structure and the technical background in order to shape a relevant solution composed by a cloud layer, software & tooling, new processes, new deployment methodology and integration with on-premises / other cloud platforms.

- Knowledge of technology to think about user experience

- Product-oriented focusing on the business outcomes

- Convinced that success is not only a matter of Technology, but a matter of People

- Never satisfied on status quo, every time looking for new way of thinking and disruptive approach, every day lost is a mischance

- Strongly committed on the 5 pillars of IT architecture providing the expected design

(Availability, Reliability, Security, Maintainability, Operability)

- 15+ years experience with several strong success in digital transformation programs and product innovations

- Consistent and end-to-end behavior mixing top/down (IT strategy) and bottom/up (Test & learn)

Naz Delam

Software Engineering Manager - LinkedIn Media

As a software engineering manager at LinkedIn, I lead a cross-functional team that drives on-platform events growth via discovery, notifications, and surfaces for all LinkedIn event types. With over 10 years of experience in web applications development, architecture, and engineering, I have a passion for creating innovative and scalable solutions that enhance user experience and engagement.

In addition to my technical role, I also work as a career coach at MentorCruise, where I mentor and guide aspiring and experienced software engineers, architects, and managers. I enjoy sharing my insights and knowledge on topics such as growth engineering, machine learning, cognitive science, and systems engineering, as well as helping others achieve their career goals and aspirations. I am also an international speaker and a frequent contributor to https://naz.dev, where I write about engineering, leadership, mentoring, and diversity.

Benjamin Potet

Senior Solutions Engineer - Make

Specialist in SaaS Solutions, Integration/Automation and API Management. My role is to help prospects and customers understand the business and technical benefits they get when using specific software in their context.

I have been working for more than 20 years in IT, starting as an application developer (Assembly code, C, C++, Java, ...), and moving to a Presales role where my experience can be leveraged to qualify prospects requirements, evangelize, explain, and demonstrate the advantages new technologies bring to the IT and, of course, to their customers: the Business.

Daniel Kocot

Head of API Experience and Operations - codecentric AG

Daniel has been part of the codecentric team since October 2016. Since the beginning of 2022 as Senior Solution Architect at the Dortmund location. Starting as a consultant with a focus on application lifecycle management, his focus shifted more and more towards APIs. In addition to numerous customer projects and his involvement in the open source world around APIs, he is also a frequent speaker as Head of API Experience & Operations.

Abhijit Dey

Vice President - Product Head API Banking - Axis Bank Ltd

Abhijit is an accomplished Product Evangelist with a rich background in the BFSI sector. With a demonstrated track record of driving innovation through API management and monetization, Abhijit has made substantial contributions to the industry. His expertise extends to the creation of an Open API framework tailored specifically for banks, showcasing his forward-thinking approach and proficiency in navigating the dynamic landscape of financial services. With a keen understanding of how technology and banking intersect, Abhijit is poised to share invaluable insights with the forum.

Mehdi Medjaoui

Founder and Chairman of Apidays Conferences, Author of Continuous API Management -

Mehdi Medjaoui is the founder of APIdays conferences series worldwide, that he started in 2012 in Paris. He is highly involved in the API community and API Industry, and is a current author, lecturer, consultant and investor in the API space. In 2011 he co-founded OAuth.io, a SaaS OAuth API middleware for OAuth integration and implementation used by 40,000+ developers, that had been acquired in December 2017. His research involves publishing the API Industry Landscape and the yearly State of Banking APIs.

Gaël Duez

Founder - Green IO

I launched Green IO podcast 🎙️ which offers responsible technologists a place to build a greener digital world, one byte at a time.For the last 15 years, I have led teams in PropTech, payment service providers, document-processing industry and I have experienced first hand the benefits that digitalization brings to people. At the same time I also lived on 3 continents and witnessed the environmental footprint of human activity on planet Earth. Between Tech for Good and sustainable IT, “Tech” is a key enabler of our ecological transition. But Tech is also a serious contributor to these ecological crises.

In 2021, I decided to focus full-time on this dual issue with a balanced approach. Putting on hold executive positions, I now help teams build greener digital products, using this much needed change as a strategic opportunity for sustainable business development.

I do so by:

- providing open-source content,

- building bridges between communities & networks

- and by leveraging collective intelligence;

based on 3 core values: respect People 🫂 , respect Science 🔬 and respect Earth 🌍.I’m always thrilled to interview doers for knowledge and feedback in the Green IO Podcast and to partner with companies looking to travel further on the Digital Sustainability road.

Erik Wilde

OAI Ambassador @ OpenAPI Initiative - API Strategist and Content Creator at Getting APIs to Work

With over 10 years of experience in the API field, I am passionate about helping organizations on their digital transformation journeys, making sure that vision, strategy, and technology are aligned, and that they are driven by well-aligned business and organizational initiatives. As an OAI Ambassador at the OpenAPI Initiative, I promote the adoption and use of open standards and best practices for API design and management, and with Getting APIs to Work, I provide consulting and training services for API programs.I have a strong background in digital transformation, API design, and API governance, and I have contributed to many publications, patents, and standards. I have also worked with various industries and sectors, such as healthcare, education, finance, and government, to help them leverage the power and potential of APIs for innovation, integration, and automation. My mission is to help organizations get APIs to work in a truly transformative way, by ensuring that they have the right APIs, and that they design and manage them in the right way.

Henry Calvert

Head of Network - GSMA

Henry joined the GSMA in December 2013, and is responsible for the delivery of the Networks programme. A key programme of the GSMA’s strategic focus, to deliver industry scale for IP Communications and 5G, whilst considering Network Economic challenges for the Mobile industry as it transitions to a 5G Era.Previously he worked for the SingTel Group and has over 20 years’ experience in the telecommunications sector, both in Networks and IT portfolios and has been involved in the deployment of mobile networks in over 10 operations across 10 different countries. Henry designed and built Optus’ 3G + LTE mobile network, all IP network and managed the product development transformation. He was the creator and board member of the network sharing Joint Venture between SingTel Optus and Vodafone Networks Pty Ltd (Australia).Henry has been a board member and Chair of the Australian Mobile Telecommunications Association (AMTA) and previously held an Executive Management Committee position in the GSMA.

Ibrahima Ndiaye

Enterprise Architect - RATP Group

Working with C- level and IT executives throughout my +15 years in IT departments in several industries such as Utilities, Banking and Telecom allowed me to enjoy transformation and change mainly because it revolves around people and behaviors management through organization. My ability to articulate each level of Entreprise Architecture (Business, Information, Solution, Technological, Governance). Interpersonal skills give me the ability to be an trusted Advisor for CIO / CTO / CDO and Business Execs.

Jonathan Le Lous

CTO - Capgemini

For more than 17 years I have been helping organizations being Lean\Agile and modernizing their App Portfolios and Software Development Life Cycle. Using DevOps, Cloud, PaaS, Containers, Microservices, API we increased delivery velocity and reducing TCO.Passionate by Open Source, as a pragmatic leader I'm used to work with partners and technologies from everywhere and building bridges between traditional IT and innovative approaches.As a community member, I have been engaged in various non-profit communities to contribute and promote Open Source. Throughout my career I have been active on producing content as Blog posts, articles, videos about technologies.

Roy Pereira

CEO & Co-Founder - Unified.to

Roy Pereira is an accomplished 4x founder and technology innovator. He is renowned for his track record of establishing successful startups in Canada and his influential senior executive roles within publicly-traded companies across North America. Roy was the visionary behind CalendarHero, an AI-powered scheduling assistant and Shiny Ads, a platform that empowered publishers to manage and monetize their ad inventory.

Today, Roy is building Unified.to, a unified API developer platform for AI applications. Under his leadership, Unified.to enables software teams to integrate once to launch multiple API integrations within hours, a breakthrough that significantly accelerates time-to-market and allows software companies to expand their lifetime revenue.

Roy remains driven by his profound passion for harnessing technology and empowering great teams to tackle real-world challenges.

Hanna Mergui

AI Engineer - Sonio

🦾 Deep Learning engineer from École Polytechnique.

Actually working at Sonio, creating deep learning models for prenatal diagnosis 👩‍🍼

Beyond academia, I'm an entrepreneur at heart, driven to innovate within the tech sphere, particularly aiming to revolutionize healthcare.

I created an artistic project two years ago. It is an artistic photo exhibition aimed at demystifying AI.

I offer positive acculturation conferences in companies, using the universal language of art 📸 (My dm are open to talk about it !)

When not exploring AI, I enjoy horse riding and diving into a good book. 🐴📚

Carlos Muñoz Ferrandis

Creator of OpenRAIL - Co-Founder & COO at Alinia AI

Hi!👋 I'm a lawyer by training focused on AI Governance & Regulation, and more specifically, on the articulation between open licensing of ML components and the governance of the latter.

My main targets are:

(i) AI governance tools (regtech tools such as automatic regulatory compliance checks for LLMs under the EU AI Act; or model cards and governance cards for LLMs);

(ii) contracts & IP licensing (such as Responsible AI Licenses);

(iii) regulation & regulatory innovation (such as EU AI Act and regulatory sandboxes);

(iii) standardization.

I have experience in different industries (AI; telecoms & IoT; DLT), and from different professional angles (public policy; legal strategy; regulatory policy; research).

I’m adamant on doing what I love to do, it has to be always both a reality and a goal. Execution and proactiveness are key for me. I am a honest, enthusiastic, creative and empathic person with a strong sense of commitment.

Juan Cruz Viotti

CTO - Intelligence.AI

Hey there! I'm a Computer Scientist with experience in startups, open-source, and academia. Some facts about me:

- I'm co-authored an O'Reilly book: Unifying Business, Data, and Code: Designing Data Products with JSON Schema

- At University of Oxford, I won the 2022 CAR Hoare prize for the best dissertation and accompanying papers in the area of Software Engineering for my research around JSON BinPack. JSON BinPack made a breakthrough on 40 years of space-efficient telecommunication and binary serialization technologies, being more space-efficient than 13 other popular technologies in every single tested case

- I'm the original author of Etcher, a popular open-source cross-platform image flasher. This desktop app is recommended by a range of GNU/Linux distributions, and was highlighted on magazine

- I lead a London-based C++ open-source research lab called Sourcemeta providing cutting-edge JSON-related technologies. There, I maintain a custom JSON parser, JSON binary technologies, and a variety of JSON Schema related projects

- I own the Learn JSON Schema (https://www.learnjsonschema.com) reference documentation website, which serves more than 7k monthly users

- At Postman, I led the development of Starship, a C++ framework to create cross-platform native applications

Peter Milne

Engineering Program Manager - Criteo

I am a seasoned IT professional with extensive experience across the full SDLC, product cycle and sales cycle.

In addition to my technical skills I have worked in pre-sales, sales and IT management. I am an excellent communicator and presenter and I have the ability to explain and “sell” the technical value proposition across cultures and languages.

I have authored and taught training classes world wide.

I have managed small and large development teams, consultant groups and education. I have developed product and sold the solution world wide through my own business and other enterprises into 31 countries, and traveled to 46 countries and 35 US states.

Australian Citizen and EU Blue Card holder.

Sabrine Bendimerad

Ambassador Google Women Techmakers - Senior AI Engineer at SAUR

I am an Applied Mathematics Engineer with 8 years of experience working on AI applications across major industries. Currently, I am focused on developing AI-based solutions for the water sector.

In addition to my engineering work, I am an entrepreneur. I design customized resources and training programs for companies in the fields of Data Science and AI. I have a strong passion for teaching, with an interest in tackling technical challenges and applying them to real-world situations.

Louis de Biesbach

Author, (TEDx) Speaker & Columnist - Consultant at Boston Consulting Group

"One of the reasons I don’t like the discussions about superintelligence is that they’re a distraction from what’s real." - Oren ETZIONI, CEO of the Allen Institute for Artificial Intelligence

Driven by a deep passion for philosophy and technology, Louis de Diesbach works as a technology ethicist and consultant. His professional and personal life is anchored by three foundational pillars: being a husband and father, working at the consultancy firm BCG, and writing for various media. At BCG, Louis specializes in the interplay between technology, governance, and strategic development, while also contributing to the firm's communications endeavours.

As a tech ethicist, Louis often writes for L'Écho and La Libre Belgique, and he regularly shares insights on the French podcast Trench Tech. His columns critically explore the ethical dimensions of technology, tackling issues from environmental impacts to regulatory frameworks and the broader societal implications of tech advancements. Louis is also the author of "Liker sa servitude" (FYP, 2023) and "Bonjour ChatGPT" (Mardaga, 2024), works that have profoundly been influenced by philosophers such as Kant, Camus, Hottois, and Turkle.
